# Tooling & environment rule

This project is **Poetry-managed** and its virtualenv is **in-project** at
`.venv/` (already created, with `arbitrator` installed editable + all dev tools).

## Hard rules

1. **Always invoke tools from `.venv`**, never the global `python`/`mypy`/`pytest`.
   The global interpreter does **not** have the project or its dev deps installed
   (`ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'arbitrator'`, `No module named mypy`).
2. Because `arbitrator` is installed **editable** in `.venv`, you do **not** need
   `PYTHONPATH=src` when using the venv interpreter.
3. **Do not use `poetry run ...`** to launch tools — in this environment it can
   hang. Call the `.venv` executables directly instead.

## Commands (Windows / PowerShell)

| Task | Command |
| ---- | ------- |
| Run all tests | `.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -q` |
| Run feature tests | `.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -k strategy -q` |
| Type check (strict) | `.venv\Scripts\mypy.exe --strict src/arbitrator` |
| Lint | `.venv\Scripts\ruff.exe check src tests` |
| Format | `.venv\Scripts\black.exe src tests` |
| Run app | `.venv\Scripts\uvicorn.exe main:app` (or `.venv\Scripts\python.exe main.py`) |

Equivalent for activated shells: `.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1`, then `pytest` /
`mypy` / `ruff` resolve to the venv binaries.

## Adding dependencies

- Add via Poetry so `pyproject.toml`/`poetry.lock` stay authoritative:
  `.venv\Scripts\poetry.exe add <pkg>` (runtime) or
  `.venv\Scripts\poetry.exe add --group dev <pkg>` (dev). Do not hand-edit
  installed packages in `.venv`.
